					<h2 class="mt-1 text-xl leading-6 font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 sm:text-2xl">Trust Account at  {facilityName} </h2>
					<p>A trust account gets created when an <a href=".">inmate is booked in {facilityName} </a>, enabling inmates to buy items and to pay various medical services and jail fees. Depositors sending cash and items must include the jail number with their details (name and address). If this information is missing on the deposited items, the facility will return the items to the depositor. Funds can be added through three modes to the inmate's account. Contact <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> for more information on inmate money accounts at {facilityName}.</p>
				
				</div>
	
	</div>
</section>
<section class="correction_section5" id="sid2">
	<div class="container">
		<br/> <h2 class="mt-1 text-xl leading-6 font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 sm:text-2xl" >Commissary Items and Online Fees </h2>
		<div class="">
					<p>Inmates are allowed to buy commissary items such as hygiene items and snacks during their incarceration. Money spent will be deducted from their account. Pricing for these items may vary depending on the <a href=".">department of correction rules</a>. Families and friends can deposit money in their inmate's account, but first, they need to create an account through the {facilityName} website to deposit money on the inmate's behalf. Money will be credited to the inmate's account once the transaction is complete. {facilityName} might charge an online fee for the deposit. Contact the facility for more information on their online fees and the amount. Please note: deposits cannot be sent over the phone by contacting {facilityName}. Contact <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> for more information!</p>
		</div>
				
	
		</div>
		
	
</section>
<section class="correction_section4" id="sid3">
