				<div class="">
					<br/> <h2 class="mt-1 text-xl leading-6 font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 sm:text-2xl">MoneyGram Transfer to {facilityName} </h2>
				<p>MoneyGram, is another easy way for families and friends to send money to an inmate. To send money, you need to contact{facilityName} for your inmate's correctional ID. Next, contact the nearest MoneyGram agent and provide them your name, inmate's name, along with their correctional ID, facility code, and the amount you want to send. Or, contact <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> to learn about other ways you can <a href="/send-money-to-inmate/">send money to an inmate!</a></p>
				
				</div>

	</div>
</section>
<section class="correction_section5" id="sid4">
	<div class="container">
		<br/> <h2 class="mt-1 text-xl leading-6 font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 sm:text-2xl">Offender Connect at {facilityName} </h2>
		<div class="">
					<p> To make <a href="/inmate-calling/">phone calls to and from {facilityName}</a>, consider creating an Offender Account for your inmate. An Offender Account allows them to make phone calls. Inmates need to register a number and provide a list of contacts for the prison to approve. When an inmate calls loved ones, the cost will be deducted from their Offender Account. Families need to contact {facilityName} for an inmate's ID, which will be required to create an account.</p>

<p>Families can contact Global Tel Link (GTL) to deposit funds in their inmate's account or by contacting Victim Assist. You can also contact <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> to learn of additional ways to <a href="/send-money-to-inmate/">deposit money</a> for your inmate.
</p>
		</div>

		</div>	
	
</section>
<section class="correction_section6" id="sid5">
	<div class="container">
	
				<div class="">
					<br/> <h2 class="mt-1 text-xl leading-6 font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 sm:text-2xl">Inmate Commissary - {facilityName}</h2>
				<p>Inmate Commissary is a fast and secure way for friends and families to send funds to an inmate. Inmates can receive these funds in{facilityName} through MoneyGram or Western Union. Please contact {facilityName} before sending commissary funds to check if your inmate has physically arrived at the facility. Funds can be transferred online or by visiting the nearest MoneyGram agent. Contact <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> for more information.</p>
 <p>Once funds are received, inmates can purchase items from the facilities provided canteen services through their inmate commissary account. Inmate accounts are funded by friends and families or through earned wages. Funds can be deposited into their account via mail, kiosk, online, or by calling our executives. To send funds through the mail, contact the {facilityName} for your inmate's registered ID, name, and the facility's details. Please contact {facilityName} for a list of available commissary items, or reach out to <a href="/">Victim Assist</a> for more information. </p>
				</div>	
			</div>
		
</section>
